RIYADH: The King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center’s (KSRelief ) air bridge is now in full swing for much-needed aid, including food, medical and shelter materials,  for those affected by the earthquake in Turkiye and Syria.
In Jandris, a town in the north of Syria, KSRelief distributed urgent relief parcels to affected residents. The center also offered medical assistance to 1,051 individuals in Gaziantep, Turkiye.
On Tuesday, the eighth aid plane from the Kingdom landed at Syria’s Aleppo International Airport carrying food, medical and shelter supplies. Over in Turkiye, another aircraft from the Kingdom touched down at Gaziantep Airport bringing medical supplies worth more than $9.6 million (SR36 million).